Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees.

Slice @demi-baguette{1} crosswise into 6 - 8 rounds. Spread slices out on a #baking sheet{}, drizzle with @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toast on top rack of oven until golden brown, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, slice @mozzarella cheese{4%ounce} into 6 - 8 rounds.

Arrange mozzarella and @prosciutto{2%ounce} on a #serving board{}. Drizzle both with @Mike's Hot Honey®{3}. Serve with toasted baguettes on the side.

> Whether you're hosting a small get-together or simply grazing, this crowd-pleasing snack couldn't be easier to throw together. We're sending everything you need: a crusty baguette, fresh mozzarella, slices of prosciutto, and Mike's Hot Honey. All you need to do? Toast, assemble, and enjoy!